{
  "texts": [
    "The synthetic images should be of different styles (modes of distribution) for each random input.",
    "In practice, the generator learns to produce synthetic images just to misguide the discriminator for being classified as real.",
    "Once the generator finds the best way to fool the discriminator by producing particular plausible images, it focuses on the generation of similar images repetitively.",
    "The discriminator gets fooled each time and classifies the synthetic images as real.",
    "Eventually, the discriminator gets stuck in this trap and is unable to get out of this trap."
  ]
}